notes: The Fallon, Stillwater and Anaho Island National Wildlife Refuges are located in northwest Nevada and are administered by the refuge administrative office in Fallon, Nevada. Together they comprise the Stillwater Wildlife Management Area (SWMA). The near normal weather conditions in 1975 had no significant affect on refuge outputs and operations. At the beginning of the year seven of the fourteen marsh units were dry. With the hot months of July and August ahead, and no expectations of increased water deliveries, it was felt that Stillwater would be providing very little in the way of waterfowl habitat during the forthcoming year. The unexpected did occur when late snowstorms hit the area. Marsh habitat was poor during the first half of the year but an increased water supply in June increased habitat acreage. Overall, waterfowl use was down due to decreased habitat caused by an inadequate water supply during the first half of the year. There was no development during the reporting period and all maintenance was routine in nature. Much of the Area continues to be badly overgrazed. Due to a reduction in water receipts most of the developed pasture was left unwatered.
